<div class="text-center">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)</h2>

    <p>Welcome to the User Support FAQ section. Here, you can find answers to common questions and issues related to the Marie Barney Boston Scholarship Foundation's Metrics Dashboard. If you need further assistance, please don't hesitate to reach out to our support team.</p>

    <div class="faq-section">
        <h4>1. How do I log into the dashboard?</h4>
        <p>To log into the dashboard, click the 'Login' button on the homepage and enter your credentials (email and password). If you haven't registered yet, you can create an account by clicking the 'Account Registration' button.</p>

        <h4>2. What should I do if I forget my password?</h4>
        <p>If you forget your password, click the 'Forgot Password' link on the login page. You will be prompted to enter your registered email address, and we will send you a password reset link.</p>

        <h4>3. How can I enable Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) for added security?</h4>
        <p>To enable Two-Factor Authentication (2FA), navigate to your account settings after logging in. Under the 'Security' section, you can activate 2FA and follow the on-screen instructions to complete the setup process.</p>

        <h4>4. How can I update my personal account details?</h4>
        <p>To update your personal account details (such as your name, email, or contact information), go to the 'Account Settings' page. Make the necessary changes and click 'Save' to update your information.</p>

        <h4>5. How can I view and filter the key metrics on the dashboard?</h4>
        <p>Once logged in, the dashboard displays key performance indicators (KPIs) by default. You can filter the metrics by date range or category using the filter options at the top of the dashboard.</p>

        <h4>6. Can I export data from the dashboard for reporting purposes?</h4>
        <p>Yes, you can export data from the dashboard in various formats (e.g., CSV, PDF). Look for the 'Export Data' button at the top of the dashboard to choose your preferred format.</p>

        <h4>7. How can I contact support if I encounter an issue not covered here?</h4>
        <p>If you're facing an issue that isn't addressed in the FAQs, you can contact support by clicking on the 'Contact Support' link in the 'Help' section. You can either submit a ticket or reach out to our support team directly via email or phone.</p>
    </div>
</div>

